
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-kerwin-http2-segments-02.txt'>
    <title>"HTTP/2 Segments", Matthew Kerwin</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-kerwin-http2-segments-02.txt</link>
    <description>This document introduces the concept of "segments" to HTTP/2, and adds a flag to the DATA frame type to allow the expression segments.  A "segment" is a contiguous block of HTTP message data that can be freely split apart and recombined at any time, allowing transmission in multiple HTTP/2 frames across network segments with smaller frame size limits without risk of permanent fragmentation when traversing network segments with much larger limits.</description>
    <dc:date>2015-02-16T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
